Alright McDonald's but I would probably do myself a favor by not coming back to this McDonald's/ trying not to go to this McDonald's location due to the fact that this restaurant is very difficult to find and fact that the food served here gets cold fast. It is very difficult to find/ locate since it is hidden inside a dark-colored dimly lit building which you wouldn't even think a McDonald's fast food restaurant would exist. There is no arch logo or guide that makes it easy to locate unlike the rest of the McDonald's Fast Food Restaurants in the Downtown Chicago area including the one even located inside the Chicago Union Station and Chicago Oglive Transportation Center. This McDonald's is located in a weird building on the second floor as the first floor of the building has almost nothing. This McDonald's is smaller than most other McDonald's since it shares the space next to Dunkin' Donuts and Burrito Beach. The service here sucks as it took so long for my order to be prepared and the food was kind of cold by the time I brought it baxk for my family to eat at the Chicago Marriott Downtown Magnificent Mile hotel my family was staying at for a conference. We thoughht this McDonald's would be convenient but it ended up actually being very inconvenient depsite the fact that it was closer to our hotel than the other McDonald's fast food restaurants in Downtown Chicago. Next time, I would rather walk further and find a McDonald's which I can find right away based on the Arch symbol rather than have to search around aimlessly for a building which looks empty and dimly lit. This building would seem more like an office building to me that decided to close it doors on the weekend. McDonald's would be the last thing that comes to my mind in this hollow building. There was also major construction around this building site when I was walking so I had an even harder time finding this McDonald's.

My family’s experience at this location was beyond terrible. The first time we came for breakfast, they messed up our orders entirely: no hash browns for our meals, cold coffee despite ordering them hot, all while giving us the wrong sandwiches. We politely confronted the employees at the front counter about this and they responded with an inappropriately bad attitude and yelled at us, as if this were our doing. Eventually, they apologized, signed our receipt, and promised us a free meal the next time we returned, but unfortunately that wasn’t the end of it all. When we returned again for breakfast 2 days later and we showed them our receipt promising a free meal, they yelled at us once again and were enraged by the fact that we had the audacity to return. I’ll never be able to comprehend how employees can treat their customers with such contempt, especially after we approached them civilly. My family and I don’t see ourselves returning to this location any time soon. It was an overall hellish experience and I would rate them 0 starts if I could. We advise you to go elsewhere if this is where you plan to dine, because you will not get the respect you deserve from the employees of this establishment.
